Hartsfield Atlanta International Airport
Annual Report 1982
Message from
Mayor Andrew Young
"No city in the continental United
States is more than five hours from
Atlanta and no major city on earth is
more than 24 hours away through our
window on the world, Hartsfield
Atlanta International.
Few cities have taken more prudent
or more successful advantage of an air-
port. With the world's second busiest
facility, the city and the region have
become a mecca for business and
tourism. Our convention industry ranks
among the top in the world and all but
a handful of the country's largest firms
maintain headquarters or regional
offices here - because our airport gives
visitors, meeting goers and business
travelers the accessibility they need.
The development by the city and
surrounding governments of more than
1,000 acres of adjacent industrial and
commercial land in the next few years
will enable the airport to maintain its
position as one of the primary economic
generators in the Southeast.
Hartsfield Atlanta International
exemplifies the city itself - built with
fiscal responsibility, providing oppor-
tunity for all races and delivering
superior service.
My thanks go to the employees of
the Department of Aviation and to the
many others in public and private
employment who have contributed to
establishing the city as an aviation giant."
